cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses deep generative models and their application in imitation learning for motor control, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of variational autoencoders (VAEs) and Generative Adversarial Imitation Learning (GAIL), which are both popular techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses reaching tasks and gaits as examples, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
